Data License — CC BY 4.0
=========================

The novel datasets distributed from this directory and on the Hugging Face
Hub (Synthetic Terms EN/PT, Wikidata Synthetic EN/PT, and the
`literature_annotations/*.csv` jargon-annotation tables) are released under
the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International license (CC BY 4.0).

Full legal text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode

In short, you are free to share and adapt this data for any purpose,
including commercially, as long as you give appropriate credit (see
"How to Cite" in the top-level README.md), provide a link to the license,
and indicate if changes were made.

Notes on underlying sources:
- Jargon terms and IPA transcriptions used to build the Wikidata Synthetic
  subsets originate from Wikidata, which is dedicated to the public domain
  under CC0 1.0 (https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/).
- Audio was synthesized with KokoroTTS (Apache License 2.0), which permits
  use and redistribution of generated audio.
- The Synthetic Terms subsets consist of entirely LLM-generated (GPT-4o),
  fictional technical terms — no real product or proprietary names.
- We are re-releasing this combined work under CC BY 4.0 for consistency
  and to make attribution requirements unambiguous. If your use case
  requires CC0-equivalent terms/IPA data on its own, see Wikidata directly.

This directory intentionally does NOT include the original audio or text
of the literature-derived datasets (CHiME-6, Earnings-22, FLEURS, GLOBE,
SPGISpeech, CORAA, LapsBM). Those remain under their original publishers'
licenses — use `scripts/1_prepare_datasets.py` to rebuild those subsets
locally after downloading the originals and agreeing to their terms.
